author: stsp
msg: Teach 'svnauth list' to list credentials matching one or more patterns.
Patterns are matched against all values of a credential set.
All patterns must match at least one value for the set to be shown.
If no patterns are provided, all credentials are listed.
For SSL certs, certificate field values are matched individually
if serf support is compiled in (serf is used to parse SSL certs).
* subversion/svnauth/svnauth.c
(cmd_table): Update 'svnauth help' output.
(parse_args): New, copied from svnadmin.
(load_cert): New helper function, split out of ...
(show_ascii_cert): ... this function.
(list_credentials_baton_t): New baton type for the list_credentials()
function, contains patterns to match.
(match_pattern, match_cert_info, match_ascii_cert): New helper functions.
(list_credentials): Before listing a credential, match it against any
provided patterns and only list it if a match is found.
(subcommand_list): Populate the new baton for list_credentials().
